<tr>
<td colspan="2" align="center" style="background:#FFD068"><small><a href="/wiki/Buddhist_terms_and_concepts" title="Buddhist terms and concepts">Buddhism Glossary</a><small><br /></small></small>
<div class="noprint plainlinksneverexpand navbar" style="background:none; padding:0; font-weight:normal;; font-size:xx-small;"><small><a href="/wiki/Template:Buddhist_term" title="Template:Buddhist term"><span title="View this template" style="">view</span></a>&#160;<span style="font-size:80%;">•</span>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Template_talk:Buddhist_term" title="Template talk:Buddhist term"><span title="Discussion about this template" style="">talk</span></a>&#160;<span style="font-size:80%;">•</span>&#160;<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Buddhist_term&amp;action=edit" class="external text" title="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Buddhist_term&amp;action=edit" rel="nofollow"><span title="Edit this template" style=";">edit</span></a></small></div>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>In <a href="/wiki/Sramana" title="Sramana" class="mw-redirect">sramanic</a> thought, <b>Nirvana</b> (<a href="/wiki/Sanskrit_language" title="Sanskrit language" class="mw-redirect">Sanskrit</a>: <span lang="sa" xml:lang="sa">निर्वाण</span>, <i><span lang="sa-Latn" title="International Alphabet of Sanskrit Transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none" xml:lang="sa-Latn">Nirvāṇa</span></i>; <a href="/wiki/Pali_language" title="Pali language" class="mw-redirect">Pali</a>: <span lang="pi" xml:lang="pi">निब्बान</span>, <i><span lang="sa-Latn" title="International Alphabet of Sanskrit Transliteration" class="Unicode" style="white-space:normal; text-decoration: none" xml:lang="sa-Latn">Nibbāna</span></i>; <a href="/wiki/Prakrit" title="Prakrit">Prakrit</a>: णिव्वाण) is the state of being free from both <a href="/wiki/Dukkha" title="Dukkha">suffering</a> and the cycle of rebirth. It is an important concept in <a href="/wiki/Buddhism" title="Buddhism">Buddhism</a> and <a href="/wiki/Jainism" title="Jainism">Jainism</a>.</p>
<p>"Nibbāna" is a <a href="/wiki/P%C4%81li" title="Pāli" class="mw-redirect">Pāli</a> word that means "blowing out" — that is, blowing out the fires of greed, hatred, and delusion.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
